<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Buddhism_and_science&amp;action=edit&amp;section=10" title="Edit section: External links">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">External links</span></h2>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://www.cttbusa.org/other2/buddhism_science.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.cttbusa.org/other2/buddhism_science.htm" rel="nofollow">Buddhism and Science</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.pnas.org/cgi/content/full/101/46/16369" class="external text" title="http://www.pnas.org/cgi/content/full/101/46/16369" rel="nofollow">Full text of 2004 paper examining effects of long-term meditation on brain function</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.psychosomaticmedicine.org/cgi/content/full/65/4/564" class="external text" title="http://www.psychosomaticmedicine.org/cgi/content/full/65/4/564" rel="nofollow">Full text of 2003 paper examining the effect of mindfulness meditation on brain and immune function</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.investigatingthemind.org/" class="external text" title="http://www.investigatingthemind.org/" rel="nofollow">The Mind and Life Conferences</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.wired.com/wired/archive/14.02/dalai.html" class="external text" title="http://www.wired.com/wired/archive/14.02/dalai.html" rel="nofollow">Buddha on the Brain - Dalai Lama on the Society for Neuroscience's annual conference</a></li>
